<br>
Sure, it would allow SOME OEing of it but not to a severe degree.  No drop = bad idea.  It also means we can't sell a special once we have outgrown it.  That just isn't right.<br>
<br>
As for using a BwT 2x your level? LOL.  Um, I guess you can get those in some hellaciously hard team missions.  I don't see how a lvl 50 could solo a 100 mission that's for sure.  From what you say, a lvl 100 could equip a 200 special.  Hard to imagine.  With the OE nerf, it's hard to see how you can get high enough to use one of these without being teamed with someone who can wrangle your skills high enough. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uralgur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ralgur</A> at: 6/24/02 11:48:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=darksong>Darksong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#660000>(6/24/02 12:38:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2037.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MA attacks</span><hr size=1> I found BwT in an individual mission out of Camelot.  BoP also seems to be popping up with regularity at QL 72-80 missions.  I will say I have more luck outside of the usual mission booths (especially in Camelot, Bliss and the outposts).  I'm not sure if this is my imagination or just the fact I tend to look at them more.<br>
<br>
A discussion I had with ARK during my debacle with a bugged mission for BwT also confirmed that BwT does, on rare occasions, appear in stores although I have never seen one.<br>
<br>
Keep looking..they are out there.  They tend to run in streaks.  I won't see any for several days; then I'll bump up against several in a row.  Just keep the faith!<br>
<br>
Darksong <p>The evil are born knowing the song..the song of the end..the song of death..the dark song</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sinda>Sinda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#660000>(6/25/02 7:41:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2037.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MA attacks</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  As for using a BwT 2x your level? LOL. Um, I guess you can get those in some hellaciously hard team missions. I don't see how a lvl 50 could solo a 100 mission that's for sure.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
That's the problem.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  From what you say, a lvl 100 could equip a 200 special. Hard to imagine. With the OE nerf, it's hard to see how you can get high enough to use one of these without being teamed with someone who can wrangle your skills high enough. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I had high enough Parry skill at level 55 to use my 112 BWT.  Now, either the BWT requirements are too low or their QL is overestimated.  Whichever.  But now, 30 levels later, I'm thinking I need a QL160 attack.  Maybe the best solution for FC is to re-evaluate the way they put QL on attacks.  I could mission for a QL90 or 100, but not a 160.<br>
<br>
And no, the specials don't fall under the OE rules.  Nor do implants.  Just armor and weapons as far as I know.<br>
