<br>
I don't know if this has been reported to Funcom. I hope it is. I have done it, and I will do it more. Also, since these attacks are made as a reward, what anyone could get, why then not to remove the NO DROP tag. As someone already said, not like some total newbie can be twinked with it anymore, considering the nowaday OE rules. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=blade>Blade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#660000>(6/27/02 5:00:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2037.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MA attacks</span><hr size=1> i got a ql 200 bop possible to use with lvl 100 if you'd get yourself good implas. also got ql 200 blabla snake (lolish 1-500 dmg and 900 MA skiill as requierement).<br>
lvl 100+ thats not a problem to get some higher lvl moves.<br>
our group is lvl 105-122 and we're doing ql 180-210 missions (ACE's are uber). i dont care about lvling, i live for pvp so i dont even use bwt. but ql 200 bop is ok and sometimes i use my bbc sky ql 180 i think(also nice because of the short calm effect)<br>
sorry but i really dont see your problems. you wont die withough much higher bwt , get yourself nice implas , nice buffs and a high-heal-spell, thats it.<br>
<br>
PS i got all the ql 200 moves of team-mission mobs.<br>
PPs stop whining, MA is one of the best professions in pvp/pvm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=softtouch>Softtouch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#660000>(6/27/02 6:36:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2037.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MA attacks</span><hr size=1> I've been using a ql 191 BoP since about level 110. It was a nice little chest or mob loot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  BTW. I just turned 131. woot! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sinda>Sinda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#660000>(6/27/02 6:48:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2037.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MA attacks</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  stop whining</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Jeez, Blade, just had to throw that in there, didn't you?<br>
<br>
Nobody's whining.  Yes, MAs are the best class in the game (IMO, and I've tried them all).  But the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  fact</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of the matter is that something isn't quite right here --<br>
<br>
In every other class, your next pet or weapon is always within your reach with mission rewards or the player barter market, within the new OE limits.  My engineer uses a pet several levels above her because she implants and buffs for it.  Ditto for my soldier's assault rifle.  But since MA attacks are NO DROP, we can't buy them on the barter market.  And since their QL is seriously skewed, a level 50 can use a QL90 BWT (I did) or a QL112 BoP or a QL121 Angel -- all of which I had when my character was half the QL of the attack.<br>
<br>
That tells me that MA attacks usable at my level are all over-valued.  If they want to take MA specials out of the shops (name three people who use Attack of Snake after level 10 and before 190) then at least make them attainable.  At level 83, my MA's QL90 BoP is now outdated.  I can probably solo a mission for a 100 if I'm real lucky, and I can probably team for one 100-110, but using FC's math my MA <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  should</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be able to use a QL150 BoP right now.  Just how the hell do I go about finding one?<br>
<br>
Sinda<br>
